WinAb

Discover what customers respond to with A/B testing

Instructions

WinAb is an A/B testing tool that allows you to test two variations of a web page to discover which one performs better. To create a test, you'll need to provide the XPath of the HTML elements you want to test for both the variant and the control.

The tool currently supports testing only two variations at a time. Make sure the variant and control segments' percentages add up to 100 for accurate test results.

To learn more about WinAb and A/B testing best practices, visit our documentation and blog on the official website.
